---
title: Deconstructed Ratatouille with Balsamic Tomatoes, Feta, and Garlic Ciabatta
description: Ratatouille is a rustic stew from southern France featuring eggplant, tomatoes, onions, bell peppers, zucchini, garlic, and herbs. Traditionally, these ingredients are simmered for hours until tender; however, our chefs decided to “deconstruct” the dish by piling the veggies high on toast. We’ve got two words for you: bon appétit!
